					span.blockquote-line I've been lucky.
					span.blockquote-line &nbsp;Opportunities don't often come along.
					span.blockquote-line &nbsp;So, when they do, you have to grab them.
			section.chapter
				.chapter-heading
					.chapter-number 04
					h2.chapter-title The Actress
				.chapter-text
					p She was cast in bit parts on stage and in films in both Holland and England before being discovered in 1952 by the French novelist Colette (1873–1954) in Monte Carlo, Monaco. Colette insisted that Hepburn play the lead role in the Broadway production of her novel #[em Gigi]. Although Hepburn's lack of experience was a problem at first, she improved steadily, and reviews of the show praised her performance. She also won a Theatre World Award for her work. This role also brought her to Hollywood’s attention.
