			section.chapter
				.chapter-heading
					.chapter-number 09
					h2.chapter-title The Companion
				.chapter-text
					p Audrey had previously been married twice, both relationships formed over a common interest. Her third and greatest love, Robert Wolders, began no differently — both had experienced tragedy in their life, and both wanted to help people. They had both acted and both decided they preferred the simpler life. Wolders and Hepburn were together from 1980 until her death in 1993. When asked why he never proposed, Wolders says that they never felt the need.
					p Wolders adds: #[em “She viewed us as being married. There were times in order to avoid confusion that she would present me as, ‘My husband, Rob,’ but never as, ‘my partner,’ or, ‘my life partner,’ or anything like that. What always pleased me or always sounded so nice was, ‘Have you met my Rob?’ Or, ‘This is my Rob.'”]
			.blockquote-container
